This isn’t just a merger of minds — it’s a masterclass in redefining the future of human-computer interaction. Jony Ive brings the soul of design, the quiet revolution of form meeting function. Altman brings the velocity of innovation, the relentless drive to push what’s possible. Together, they’re not building a product — they’re building a new paradigm.

And if Apple’s stock reacted, it’s not because they’re scared. It’s because they’re watching.